This paper deals with the design of mechanisms in game theory, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to design these mechanisms, which could potentially fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of statistical techniques to analyze the performance of the mechanisms, which could fall under the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
